<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-0919 </DOCNO><TEXT>Through the 1970's to the present, the expansion of the mining industryand pressures placed upon it by the interaction with other land usersincreasingly challenged existing legislation. To redress this situation,the State Government presently is conducting one of the most substantialreviews of the Queensland Mining Act and Regulations ever undertaken.As part of the review, the Government, in May of this year, releaseda Green Paper to provide a basis for discussion and to encourage contributionsfrom interested parties. This paper is designed to assist in understandingthe provisions of the current legislation and the broad issues addressedin the Green Paper.</TEXT></DOC>